{
  "stem": "24346.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The workers who worked in these resorts, whether it was a tailor resort, a shoe resort, or, or carpentry-- we used to make, for the Germans, furniture.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We used to make boxes for ammunition.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so they were paid with ghetto money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the food that they sent in, he opened up stores, and they gave out ration cards, and so and so much.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But it was a diet-- it was a starvation diet, that's what.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The food that they sent in per person was not enough to, to fill your stomach-- meaning, throughout the four years that I was in the Lodz ghetto, I didn't have one day that I should say I was full.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And for four years, I was hungry-- every day, every week, every month, for four years, I was hungry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Identical-- my parents is a different question.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother and my brother-- because one of my oldest brothers, Jacob, he got married around 1937, so he wasn't with us anymore.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also, it was said in the First World War, it was better to be in a smaller town than the big city.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Big cities used to be bombarded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had an inheritance in Krasnik Lubelski, what I mentioned, where my mother came from.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father said, let's go to that town, it's a small town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We wouldn't be bombarded, hopefully.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It used to be easier-- we could go closer to farmers, maybe buy some food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father went there-- I went there, on the same wagon-- horse and buggy, no train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was quite a few days a ride to get there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother, and one brother were left behind-- the next one to me-- Lieb-- he should tend the store and watch the apartment.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
